Package au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.process

Class AbstractProcess

java.lang.Object
au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime.process.AbstractProcess
All Implemented Interfaces:
Spatialized<DynamicSpace<SystemComponent>>, MultipleDataTrackerHolder<Metadata>, TwProcess, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sealable
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractRelationProcess, ComponentProcess
public abstract class AbstractProcess extends Object implements TwProcess, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sealable, MultipleDataTrackerHolder<Metadata>, Spatialized<DynamicSpace<SystemComponent>>
An ancestor class for 3Worlds "Processes". The descendant Processes implement different ways of looping on SystemComponents or SystemRelations to apply user-defined functions.
Author:
gignoux - 10 mars 2017

    • addFunction

      public abstract void addFunction​(TwFunction function)
      For use in descendant Process classes. This method the user-computed coordinates according to space edge effect corrections. This method is called at creation of a SystemComponent only, so coordinates may be constants or driver values.
      Parameters:
      sc - the SystemComponent to locate
      cont - the component container, to compute its label
